<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
  <title>KarmaForge</title>
</head>
<body>
  <header>
    <h1 id="title">KarmaForge</h1>
      <h3 id="welcome-message">Boost your community's <span> Karma-- <span>commit to donate or sell your old stuff.</h3>
    <p id="instructions">How does it work?</p>
    <ol id="how-to-forge">
      <li>Choose your city.</li>
      <li>Find a thing you no longer need.</li>
      <li>See about how much you'd get auctioning on ebay (and if anyone would want it)</li>
    </ol>

    <p>Then what? Choose to donate your stuff and forge karma for yourself and your community! Why? Because giving your old things away benefits everyone. And, it's fun! Each item has a karmic value that's revealed and added to your karma points and your city's whenever you choose to donate.</p>

    <p>Want to try to sell it? That's cool. Choose sell and you'll go to ebay's sign up page to try your luck!</p>

    <p>Ready?</p>
  </header>
    <button id="enter">Forge!</button>
      <div id="error-message">
      </div>

      <div id="location">
      <p>I'm forging karma for: </p>
        <%= form_for :location do |f| %>
          <%= f.text_field :city, placeholder: "City name", value: @location.city %>
          <%= f.text_field :state, placeholder: "State abbreviation", value: @location.state %>
          <%= f.submit "Next" %>
        <% end %>
      </div>

    <div id="item-search">
      <p>Describe your item-- some good search terms include: name, brand, material, year, or condition.  Like Shrek DVD 2001</p>
       <%= form_for :item do |f| %>
       <%= f.text_field :name, placeholder: "Enter Item Keywords" %>
       <%= f.submit "Fetch eBay" %>
       <% end %>

       <button id="item_save">Next</button>
    </div>

    <div id="ebay-display">
    <button id="donate">Donate</button>
      <form action="http://www.ebay.com" method="get">
        <button id="sell">Sell</button>
      </form>
    </div>

    <div id="transaction-display">
    </div>

</body>
</html>

